  "report": {
    "narrative": [
      "Scheduler pressure in the 2026-03-01..2026-03-24 window shows a clear “two-partition backlog” pattern: mi3001x and mi2104x account for the vast majority of pending demand at the evaluation snapshot, while several other GPU-family partitions are fully saturated (CPU saturation=1.0) but do not exhibit a large pending queue.\n\nWhere pending jobs are concentrated (strong evidence):\n- mi3001x: 36 pending (largest backlog)\n- mi2104x: 26 pending (second-largest backlog)\n- All other partitions in the preview are minor at this snapshot: mi3008x=2, mi3258x=2, and mi2508x/mi3508x/mi2101x/devel=1 each.\n\nWhich GPU families/partitions are saturated (as reported by partitionCpuSaturation; note this is CPU saturation, not explicitly GPU saturation):\n- Fully saturated (1.0): mi3008x, mi3258x, mi3508x\n- High but not full: mi3001x (0.75), mi2508x (0.7), staff (~0.656), mi2104x (~0.619)\n- Low: devel (0.25)\n\nWhat it implies:\n- Primary user-visible bottlenecks are mi3001x and mi2104x: these partitions are where demand is clearly exceeding immediately available capacity (large pending counts).\n- Cluster utilization appears broadly high: multiple partitions at 1.0 saturation suggests substantial continuous load, even where queues are small.\n- Possible scheduling/constraint imbalance (medium/low confidence): the mismatch of “full saturation but low pending” (mi3008x/mi3258x/mi3508x) vs “large pending” (mi3001x/mi2104x) can occur if workloads are highly partition-specific (GPU model/topology, memory requirements, feature constraints, access controls) or if policy/priority prevents queue buildup. Confirming imbalance vs true scarcity requires job constraint/GRES request and node availability data, which is not present in the preview.\n\nConfidence caveat: the saturation metric shown is CPU-based at the partition level; interpreting it as GPU-family saturation is directional but not definitive without GPU allocation/utilization (GRES) metrics."
    ],
    "highlights": [
      "Backlog concentration: mi3001x=36 pending and mi2104x=26 pending dominate the queue at the snapshot.",
      "Full saturation partitions: mi3008x, mi3258x, mi3508x are at saturation=1.0 yet show only 1–2 pending jobs each.",
      "Interpretation: likely capacity pinch for mi3001x/mi2104x specifically; other partitions may be busy but not experiencing the same submission pressure or may be policy/constraint-limited.",
      "Key caveat: partitionCpuSaturation reflects CPU saturation, not direct GPU saturation—needs GRES allocation/utilization to confirm GPU-family saturation."
